egin\": 788, \"end\": 799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_league_team\", \"score\": 0.6087610168011983, \"rank\": 0.632693475971149, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_league_team\"}, {\"begin\": 802, \"end\": 814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finn_Butcher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Finn Butcher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finn_Butcher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finn_Butcher\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Clarke\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 593}, {\"ngram\": \"a three-time world champion\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 622}, {\"ngram\": \"his gold medal\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 642}, {\"ngram\": \"the ramp\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 692}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's race\", \"from\": 696, \"to\": 710}, {\"ngram\": \"Noah Hegge\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 741}, {\"ngram\": \"second place\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 780}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moments earlier, Woods' decision to go for broke almost cost her a place on the podium as she sunk from second place to fourth and last before a late twist saw Germany's Elena Lilik disqualified and gave the 28-year-old her second bronze medal of the Games.\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 1074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 977, \"end\": 984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9989194212398018, \"rank\": 0.0005257189739179142, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 987, \"end\": 992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Police_of_The_Wire\", \"score\": 0.9999999763831514, \"rank\": 2.221714839300947e-08, \"text\": \"Elena\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Police_of_The_Wire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Police_of_The_Wire\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Woods' decision\", \"from\": 834, \"to\": 849}, {\"ngram\": \"broke\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 865}, {\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 889}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 903}, {\"ngram\": \"second place\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 933}, {\"ngram\": \"a late twist\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"the 28-year-old her second bronze medal\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1060}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1073}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The no-holds-barred sport, in which everything bar dangerous contact is allowed, sends four competing racers off a high ramp simultaneously and pitches them down a broiling 200-metre course involving a series of gates and an obligatory eskimo roll.\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1324, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The no-holds-barred sport\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1101}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"dangerous contact\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1144}, {\"ngram\": \"four competing racers\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1184}, {\"ngram\": \"a high ramp\", \"from\": 1189, \"to\": 1200}, {\"ngram\": \"a broiling 200-metre course\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"a series\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1284}, {\"ngram\": \"gates\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"an obligatory eskimo roll\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Woods, who had kept out of danger and cruised through her previous heats, made a strong start but a bid to effectively take out herAustralianrival, Noemi Fox, almost backfired.\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1474, \"end\": 1479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noemi_(singer)\", \"score\": 0.96